Package com.github.shiftac.upartier.network

Interface ByteArrayIO

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ACKInf, Block, BlockFetchInf, BString, ByteArrayIOList, CountFetchInf, GenericFile, IDFetchInf, Image, LoginInf, MessageInf, MsgFetchInf, PlainMessage, Post, PostFetchInf, PostJoinInf, SynObject, User, UserFetchInf

    public interface ByteArrayIO
    We recommend that every class that implements ByteArrayIO give a comment about how its data is serialized when writing to a byte array. We use a C struct-like grammar to do that, while we assume there's no aligning constraints and thus we won't get any padding bytes. An example is: 
     class User
 {
     int id;
     int age;
     byte gender;
     short mlen;
     byte[mlen] mailAccount;
     byte nlen;
     byte[nlen] nickname;
     Image profile;
     int postCount;
 }
    Fields are listed using their types and names. For fields that correspond to a member in the object itself, their names should exactly match the names of the members. For fields that are not, there's no constraint on which names should be used. We also give a possible list of types:
    • byte: 8-bit integer;
    • short: 16-bit integer;
    • int: 32-bit integer;
    • long: 64-bit integer;
    • type[len]: Array with length == len. len can either be a integer value defined previously or a constant.
    • type[]: Array with unknown length. Length of it can be decided when calling read() with len specified: its length is len - buffer length used by previous fields. This field can only be the last field of a object.
    • Classname: An object that implements ByteArrayIO.
    • Bitfield: we use Big-Endian represent here.
    See Also:
    User, PlainMessage
